blog_post.prompt_template:
Write a comprehensive blog post about: {prompt}

Target audience: {target_audience}
Tone: {tone}
Key points to cover: {context_summary}

Structure the post with:
1. Compelling headline
2. Engaging introduction
3. 3-5 main sections with subheadings
4. Strong conclusion
5. Clear call-to-action

Optimize for SEO and ensure high readability.

social_media.prompt_template:
Create a {platform} post about: {prompt}

Target audience: {target_audience}
Tone: {tone}
Context: {context_summary}

Make it engaging, include relevant hashtags, and add a call-to-action.
Character limit: {max_chars}

email.prompt_template:
Write professional email content for: {prompt}

Target audience: {target_audience}
Tone: {tone}
Context: {context_summary}

Include:
1. Compelling subject line
2. Personal greeting
3. Clear, concise body (max 400 words)
4. Strong call-to-action
5. Professional closing

Make it scannable and action-oriented.

marketing_copy.prompt_template:
Create compelling marketing copy for: {prompt}

Target audience: {target_audience}
Tone: {tone}
Key selling points: {context_summary}

Focus on:
1. Clear value proposition
2. Customer benefits (not just features)
3. Social proof if available
4. Strong call-to-action
5. Persuasive but authentic language

product_description.prompt_template:
Write a compelling product description for: {prompt}

Target audience: {target_audience}
Tone: {tone}
Product details: {context_summary}

Structure:
1. Attention-grabbing headline
2. Key benefits (what's in it for the customer)
3. Important features
4. Technical specifications if relevant
5. Clear call-to-action

Make it scannable with bullet points and emphasize customer value.

press_release.prompt_template:
Write a professional press release for: {prompt}

Company info: {target_audience}
Key details: {context_summary}

Follow standard press release format:
1. Compelling, newsworthy headline
2. Strong lead paragraph (who, what, when, where, why)
3. Supporting details in body paragraphs
4. Relevant quotes from key stakeholders
5. Company boilerplate

Write in third person, use objective tone, focus on newsworthiness.
